WARNING!!! My mother bought life insurance with this company NEW YORK LIFE. She has been struggling to pay her insurance payment every month and still has paid it loyally for ten years. Just the other day at the ten year mark, she got a notice that her payments which were originally $52.00 per month just shot up to $288.00 per month because (they told her) after ten years her premium automatically increases. She was originally told her $52.00 payment was locked in 10 years ago by her sales rep. Absolutely disgusting!!! I always wondered what the catch was. 

From what I understand now is that she now has a choice to either pay $288. a month or change her plan to have higher payments for less insurance, or drop this new ridiculous payment and have no insurance. I am trying to understand why anyone would ever buy life insurance if it goes up to unaffordible amounts when you are less likely to be able to afford it and need it most. Isnt this equivelent to dumping your money down the toilet. Totally misrepresented...I was thinking the gamble was committing to the monthly payment and sticking to it for the rest of your life. 

How terrible it is when you make sacrifices for your family for so long thinking about their well being and you find out it was all for NOTHING!!!

READ THE FINE PRINT OR HAVE AN ATTORNEY INTERPRET ANY COMMITMENTS SUCH AS THIS...CROOKS!

My husband, Peyton, died of esophageal cancer two years ago.  He prepared for his death in every way possible from having total maintenance done on every item in our home to writing a book for me called “After Peyton” with lists of who to call for every eventuality and the appropriate sequence.   His preparation made the difference in my survival.
I learned through my experience that our society is sadly ignorant of death.  We hide from it.  We ignore it.  We fear it and we fear those who are touched by it.  Every instance is termed a shock, yet it is the one constant in our lives after birth.   I want to help change that.  I started a Facebook page on the second anniversary of Peyton’s death titled “Until Death Do We Part”. https://www.facebook.com/untildeathdowe 
 My goal is to change public knowledge, attitudes and behavior towards dying, death and bereavement through open communications and shared experience.  I plan for this to be a repository for information and an open forum for discussion.  
You probably will not want to visit this page today, tomorrow or even this year.  Just know it is there if you need help or a place to talk.

data.message: Well, its been four years since you entrusted me with the business of your life and it is 99% complete. What an education for me in facing my own mortality. Your preparation has taught me much in being personally prepared. The irony is that which was the least was the most troublesome. And the biggest has been the most petty. I cynically assume they prey on the clients with small holdings knowing that they will stop pursuing their claim or die. I promise you Linda, they have every piece of documentation known to man and still insist on more. I will never recommend New York Life Insurance to anyone I know. The next step will be the State insurance commissioner and then legal action. Odd isn't it? I think of you every day Linda Aldous and miss you and love you dearly. Your brother (ranting) Gary

NYLife, however seems to "assume" a better knowledge. Apparently my correspondence to them in regard to this issue fell on deaf ears.
